# Chronically Failing Questions - Top 10 Worst Performers
#
# These questions consistently fail across 15+ evaluation runs with:
# - Low context_recall (< 40%)
# - Low answer_correctness (< 50%)
# - High RAG_BYPASS rate (LLM uses parametric knowledge instead of contexts)
#
# Root causes identified:
# 1. okp-mcp retrieves lifecycle/policy docs instead of technical docs
# 2. No version filtering (RHEL 5/6/7 docs retrieved for RHEL 10 questions)
# 3. Missing documentation (Kea DHCP, rpm-ostree not well indexed)
# 4. Over-retrieval without semantic deduplication
#
# Use this config to:
# - Test okp-mcp improvements (lifecycle de-boost, version filtering)
# - Measure baseline before/after changes
# - Focus on questions that matter most for accuracy
#
# Expected improvements after fixes:
# - context_recall: 35% → 70%+
# - answer_correctness: 45% → 75%+
# - Lifecycle docs per query: 6.5 → < 2
#
# ==============================================================================
# TOP 10 CHRONICALLY FAILING QUESTIONS
# Sorted by failure rate (worst first)
# ==============================================================================

